text: Omega (Ѡ ѡ or Ѡ ѡ; italics: Ѡ ѡ or Ѡ ѡ) is a letter used in the early Cyrillic alphabet. It came from the Greek Omega, and stands for the number 800. The lowercase version of Omega is different and also looks like the Latin letter W. Category:Cyrillic letters Category:Vowel letters
title: Omega (Cyrillic)
